    {
      "id": "96377f07_315c39c9",
      "file_path": "csit/config/apex-pdp/OnapPfConfig.json",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 8,
      "message": "Looks good. Still a question: I see you wrote a python script to do find and replace on all config files. Setting these as an environment variable and using something like ${HTTPS_ENABLED} doesn't work?\nSimilar to how the helm charts work https://github.com/onap/oom/blob/master/kubernetes/policy/components/policy-apex-pdp/resources/config/OnapPfConfig.json#L7 \nMaybe you tried it already and it doesn't pick up the variables in docker compose?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2022-02-16 13:27:24.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "fdd18b51_97643f70",
      "file_path": "csit/config/apex-pdp/OnapPfConfig.json",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 8,
      "message": "I tried this method, but then they were not \"reloaded\" with the values, so got errors with \"can't process $HTTPS_ENABLED\" when parsing the configuration files within the containers. sourcing them also didn't work.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7625,
        "name": "Adheli Tavares",
        "display_name": "Eli Tavares",
        "email": "adheli.tavares@est.tech",
